Substitution cipher: replacement of letters
- Caesar cipher: letters shifted by fixed distance along alphabet
Transposition cipher: permutation of letters
- Scytale: written diagonally down, read one line at time
- Rail fence cipher: written diagonally down and up, read one line at time
- Route cipher: written in grid, read following specific path
- Columnartransposition: written in fixed-length rows, read  by columns in some order
